library("rjson")

Fetch prices

# Look for files of interest
files <- list.files(path = "tmp", pattern = "*.json", full.names = TRUE)
stopifnot(length(files) > 0)

ignore <- mapply(print, files)
## [1] "tmp/BCH.json"
## [1] "tmp/BCHABC.json"
## [1] "tmp/BTC.json"
## [1] "tmp/EOS.json"
## [1] "tmp/ETC.json"
## [1] "tmp/ETH.json"
## [1] "tmp/LTC.json"
## [1] "tmp/REP.json"
## [1] "tmp/XLM.json"
## [1] "tmp/XRP.json"
## [1] "tmp/ZRX.json"
prices <- c()
extract <- function(f){
  raw = fromJSON(file = f)
  p <- c(); for (observation in raw$Data) p <- c(p, observation$close)
  p
}

prices <- as.data.frame(mapply(extract, files))
summary(prices)

Linear regression

for (y in prices) {

  x <- 1:length(y)
  relation <- lm(y ~ x)

  # plot(n)
